text: Edward Norman Fadeley (December 13, 1929 - August 30, 2015) was an American attorney and former politician in the state of Oregon. He was the 88th Associate Justice of the Oregon Supreme Court. Previously he served in both the Oregon House of Representatives and the Oregon State Senate, serving one session as President of the Oregon Senate. ==References== Category:1929 births Category:2015 deaths Category:Deaths from heart failure Category:American judges Category:Politicians from Missouri Category:Politicians from Oregon
